<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2248] fileinstall does not restart bundles when the underlying file is modified</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2248</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As I reported earlier in the forum, I found some strange behavior with fileinstall-2.0.8. If I modify a jar in watched directory, fileinstall stops the corresponding bundle and does not restart it until the framework is restarted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To reproduce this:&lt;br/&gt;
Copy a new bundle to watched directory.&lt;br/&gt;
Wait for fileinstall to install and start it.&lt;br/&gt;
Now modify the bundle jar in watched dir.&lt;br/&gt;
You shall see the bundle is either in RESOLVED state or INSTALLED state now depending on whether this bundle participates in class loading or not.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
